'''European DataWarehouse GmbH''' is part of the [[ABS Loan Level Initiative|ABS Loan Level Data initiative]] established by the [[European Central Bank]] that is engaged in providing [[Data Warehousing]] services and full disclosure for investors in [[Asset-Backed Securities]] (ABS).<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news|last1=Mayre|first1=Anil|title=Euro ABS DataWarehouse investors offered incentive scheme|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/europe-abs/euro-abs-data-warehouse-investors-offered-incentive-scheme-idUSL5E8EF6JQ20120315|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=March 15, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Eficiencia">{{cite news|title=La Comisión Europea da un paso más en su apoyo a las Hipotecas Verdes|url=https://www.eseficiencia.es/2017/11/22/comision-europea-da-paso-mas-apoyo-hipotecas-verdes|publisher=Eficiencia|date=November 22, 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Company Overview of European DataWarehouse GmbH|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=180107009|website=[[Bloomberg.com]]|accessdate=December 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=European DataWarehouse sorgt für Transparenzgewinn von Auto-ABS-Transaktionen|url=https://www.tsi-kompakt.de/2013/09/european-datawarehouse-sorgt-fur-transparenzgewinn-von-auto-abs-transaktionen/|publisher=TSI-kompakt.de|date=September 26, 2013}}</ref> It provides an open platform for users to access Asset-Backed Security data.
It is the first centralised data repository in Europe for collecting, validating and making accessible to download point-by-point, institutionalised and asset class specific loan-level data (LLD) for [[Asset-Backed Securities]] (ABS) transactions.<ref name="lld">{{cite news|title=European DataWarehouse: European Loan Level Data: Smart Usage Beyond Asset-Backed Securities|url=http://www.risktech-forum.com/research/european-datawarehouse-european-loan-level-data-smart-usage-beyond-asset-ba|publisher=RiskTech Forum|date=November 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=1010data, Inc. and European DataWarehouse GmbH Partner to Increase Transparency of European Asset Backed Securities|url=https://1010data.com/company/news-events/press-releases/1010data-inc-and-european-datawarehouse-gmbh-partner-to-increase-transparency-of-european-asset-backed-securities/|publisher=1010data.com|date=June 4, 2014}}</ref> European DataWarehouse helps to facilitate risk assessment and improve transparency for European ABS deals.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kanoni|first1=Eirini|last2=Schaber|first2=Markus|title=European DataWarehouse: An initiative to improve transparency for European securitisation market|url=https://eurodw.eu/wp-content/uploads/Kanoni_Schaber_EuropeanDataWarehouse.pdf|website=eurodw.eu|format=pdf}}</ref>
== History == European DataWarehouse was founded in January 2012 for the purpose of facilitating risk assessment and improving transparency in European Asset-Backed Security (ABS) deals.<ref>{{cite news|title=REFILE-ECB launches structured transparency programme|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/ecb-abs-disclosure/refile-ecb-launches-structured-transparency-programme-idUSL5E8MRBBK20121130|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=November 30, 2012}}</ref>
== Responsibilities == European DataWarehouse's responsibilities include ensuring that ABS market data is openly accessible and that all transactions are recorded. A key aim of European DataWarehouse is to instil trust back into the ABS market, which has been a problem in recent times. The [[European Central Bank]] is set to make compliance with loan-level data disclosure compulsory before it will accept [[asset-backed securities]] as collateral for financing.<ref name="Reuters"/><ref name="lld"/><ref name="Eficiencia"/>
== Boards == ED has three decision-making bodies and 17 shareholders: *'''Supervisory Board''': the main decision-making body. It comprises the shareholder members and governors/observers from the [[European Central Bank|ECB]] and NCB. It is responsible for strategy and monitoring ED’s operations. *'''Pricing Committee''': sets the fee structure for ED customers and consists of 8 members of the ABS industry. *'''ED Management''': represented by CEO Christian Thun.
The ED shareholders are: {| class="wikitable" |[[Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria S.A.]] |- |[[Banco Santander S.A.]] |- |[[BNP Paribas|BNP Paribas S.A.]] |- |[[CaixaBank]] S.A. |- |[[Crédit Agricole]] S.A. |- |[[Crédit Foncier de France]] |- |Creditreform Rating AG |- |[[DBRS]] |- |Dutch Securitisation Association |- |Instituto de Crédito Oficial |- |[[Intesa Sanpaolo]] S.P.A. |- |Moody's Group Cyprus Limited |- |[[Sapient Corporation|Sapient Global Market]] |- |[[Société Générale]] S.A. |- |True Sale International |- |[[UniCredit]] S.P.A. |- |[[Unione di Banche Italiane]] S.C.P.A. |}
== Awards == The company received the Banking Technology Award for the Best Industry Infrastructure Initiative in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=European DataWarehouse Wins "Best Industry Infrastructure Initiative"|url=http://lcmpartners.eu/news/european-datawarehouse-wins-best-industry-infrastructure-initiative/|publisher=LCM Partners|date=December 14, 2012}}</ref>
