'''Herman Hu''' ([[Traditional Chinese characters|Chinese]]: 胡曉明) (b. Feb 1954)<ref>[http://news.takungpao.com.hk/hkol/politics/2012-12/1331171_2.html Ta Kung Pao]</ref> was the Chairman of the Council of [[City University of Hong Kong]] from 2012 to 2017. Hu is a Member of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference ([[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference|CPPCC]]) and Hong Kong deputy to the 12th & 13th National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China ([[National People's Congress|NPC]]).<ref>[http://news.takungpao.com.hk/hkol/politics/2012-12/1331171_2.html Ta Kung Pao]</ref> Hu was one of the first Election Committee members to nominate [[Leung Chun-ying]] for the post of Chief Executive of Hong Kong.<ref>[http://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1037124/cy-leung-names-his-nominator-city-university-council-chairman C.Y. Leung names his nominator as City University council chairman (SCMP)]</ref><ref>[http://www.scmp.com/article/575135/new-election-committee-makeup THE NEW ELECTION COMMITTEE MAKEUP (SCMP)]</ref> Hu is the head of Ryoden Development Ltd and is the son of [[Hu Fa-kuang]].
